A toddler slipped and fell into the cheetah exhibit at the Cleveland Metroparks Zoo on Saturday . 
  His mother was holding him and another child when he fell between 10 to 12ft and into the pit . 
  The child was rescued by his parents before firefighters and paramedics arrived on the scene . 
  He suffered minor bumps and bruises and is in stable condition at the hospital . 
  The zoo plans to press child endangering charges against the child's mother . 
 